Privacy Compliance

GDPR Compliance

strategic management

First and foremost, in digital era, privacy protection is of paramount importance for building and maintaining long-lasting customer relationship. By the EU General Data Privacy Regulation (GDPR), you are solely a holder of personal data used for the well-defined, customer acknowledged & approved purposes, and you are fully responsible for any misuse, any loss or any data breach of personal data. Only secondly, you should be fully aware of GDPR’s significant fines threats, amounting up to 4% of group level turnover.

Companies should be fully aware of its personal data processing risks across the operations in any given moment. Setting up roles and responsibilities as well as policies and procedures enables you to pro-actively tackle data privacy risks in a contemporary and profound way.

Benefits:

Ensure timely and effective management of personal data

Raise awareness

Customer loyalty

Reduce risk exposure to data breaches, their misuse and mishandling

Clear command line in case of data breaches

DPIA

strategic management

Benefits:

- Transparency: Improves how you use information; Helps individuals understand how and why their information is being used.

- Trust: Publish your DPIA to build trust

- Cost saving: Minimise the amount of information you collect.

- Awareness: Increase awareness of privacy and data protection issues within your organisation.

- Compliance: Comply with GDPR obligations

- Assurance: Individuals can be reassured your project has followed best practice.

- Risk reduction: Identify and reduce privacy risks.

Processing personal data has become a new standard. Everybody is engaged in some sort of content personalization; hence companies use as much personal data they can.

Data Privacy Impact Assessment is used to assesses the likelihood and impact of a compromise to the confidentiality, integrity and availability of personal data within each customer-centric process around the company.
